From be285cde3f52571087816759220a68cb994d9307 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Stenberg <daniel@haxx.se>
Date: Wed, 5 Apr 2006 12:35:48 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Michele Bini modified the NTLM code to work for his "weird
 IIS case" (http://curl.haxx.se/mail/lib-2006-02/0154.html) by adding the NTLM
 hash function in addition to the LM one and making some other adjustments in
 the order the different parts of the data block are sent in the Type-2 reply.
 Inspiration for this work was taken from the Firefox NTLM implementation.

I edited the existing 21(!) NTLM test cases to run fine with these news. Due
to the fact that we now properly include the host name in the Type-2 message
the test cases now only compare parts of that chunk.
